---
/**
 * About page — /about
 *
 * Conveys Ari's design philosophy and working style, drawn from the
 * canonical interview-context.md. Targets hiring managers at premium
 * product companies who want to understand how Ari thinks and leads.
 *
 * The layout mirrors the case study header structure (eyebrow, title,
 * lede, body) so the site feels cohesive. Copy sits in a narrow reading
 * column matching the prose width used in case studies.
 */
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Ari Zilnik — design leader who builds teams, ships AI products, and stays close to the work."
>
  {/* Same content shell as every other page for horizontal padding parity
      with the site header. The inner wrapper caps content to the reading
      measure and centers it inside the shell, matching the centered prose
      axis used on case studies so the "About me" title sits under the
      header's visual midpoint instead of hanging off the left edge. */}
  <section
    class="mx-auto px-6"
    style="
      max-width: var(--theme-content-width);
      padding-top: var(--theme-space-7);
      padding-bottom: var(--theme-space-7);
    "
  >
  <div class="mx-auto" style="max-width: var(--theme-prose-width);">
    {/* Eyebrow for rhythm consistency with work/[slug] and work/index */}
    <p
      class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase"
      style="
        color: var(--theme-text-tertiary);
        letter-spacing: var(--theme-tracking-wider);
        margin-bottom: var(--theme-space-2);
      "
    >
      About
    </p>

    <h1
      class="font-heading"
      style="
        color: var(--theme-text-primary);
        font-weight: var(--theme-weight-heading);
        letter-spacing: var(--theme-tracking-tight);
        line-height: var(--theme-leading-tight);
        font-size: var(--theme-text-5xl);
      "
    >
      About me
    </h1>

    <div
      class="font-sans"
      style="
        color: var(--theme-text-secondary);
        font-size: var(--theme-text-lg);
        line-height: var(--theme-leading-relaxed);
        margin-top: var(--theme-space-5);
      "
    >
      <p>
        I'm <span class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Ari Zilnik</span>.
        I lead design teams and ship products. Currently
        <span class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Head of Design at Join</span>,
        a project management platform for construction.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--theme-space-3);">
        I care more about making great things than about titles or lanes. If the
        highest-impact thing I can do on a given day is run a research session, I
        run it. If it's unblocking an engineer with a prototype, I build the
        prototype. If it's presenting to the CEO to change a product direction, I
        make the case. My job is to do whatever moves the work forward.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--theme-space-3);">
        I've spent most of my career in ambiguous, zero-to-one environments:
        <span class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">founding designer at Blockdaemon</span>
        (crypto infrastructure for Goldman Sachs and Microsoft),
        <span class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">lead designer at Gradle</span>
        (developer tools for Netflix and Salesforce), and now leading design at Join.
        The common thread is taking something undefined and bringing structure
        to it.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--theme-space-3);">
        I lead by example. I stay close to the work, run crits, and tailor
        mentorship to each person's level and career goals. At Join, I inherited
        a junior team and upskilled them to run research projects and build AI
        prototypes independently. At Blockdaemon, I grew the design org from one
        person (me) to seven. I believe the best design leaders still ship.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--theme-space-3);">
        I've worked fully remote since 2017, long before the pandemic made it
        normal. Async communication, written decisions, and timezone-aware
        collaboration aren't skills I had to learn for remote work. It's how I
        naturally operate.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--theme-space-3);">
        Outside of work, I automate things in my house, fix up vintage audio
        equipment, and spend time with my two kids in Toronto.
      </p>
    </div>

    {/* CTA — sits in the same column as the prose, so the line of action
        aligns visually with the text above it. */}
    <div style="margin-top: var(--theme-space-6);">
      <a
        href="mailto:ari@ari.design"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-7 py-3 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors"
        style="background-color: var(--theme-text-primary); color: var(--theme-bg);"
        data-goatcounter-click="contact-about"
      >
        Get in touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
